External system requirements
============================

faissR requires the FAISS C++ library. FAISS is mandatory for all builds,
including CPU-only builds. The package does not vendor FAISS.

NVIDIA CUDA, RAPIDS cuVS, and RAPIDS libcugraph are not required for a
CPU-only FAISS build. They are required when the user requests a GPU-enabled
build.

Required for all platforms
--------------------------

- R development headers.
- A C++20-capable compiler.
- A Fortran compiler.
- FAISS C++ headers and library.

If FAISS is not in a standard compiler/linker path or visible through
pkg-config, set FAISS_HOME to a prefix containing:

  include/faiss/Index.h
  lib/libfaiss.so      on Linux
  lib/libfaiss.dylib   on macOS

Example:

  FAISS_HOME=/path/to/faiss R CMD INSTALL .

Linux CPU-only build
--------------------

Install or build FAISS with GPU support disabled. Then install faissR with:

  FAISS_HOME=/path/to/faiss-cpu \
  FAISSR_USE_CUDA=0 \
  FAISSR_USE_CUVS=0 \
  FAISSR_USE_CUGRAPH=0 \
  R CMD INSTALL .

Linux NVIDIA GPU build
----------------------

Install a compatible NVIDIA driver, CUDA toolkit, FAISS build, and any RAPIDS
libraries required by the desired routes.

Strict FAISS GPU / CUDA-native build:

  CUDA_HOME=/usr/local/cuda \
  FAISS_HOME=/path/to/faiss-gpu \
  FAISSR_REQUIRE_CUDA=1 \
  R CMD INSTALL .

Strict direct cuVS build:

  CUDA_HOME=/usr/local/cuda \
  FAISS_HOME=/path/to/faiss \
  CUVS_HOME=/path/to/rapids-or-cuvs \
  FAISSR_REQUIRE_CUDA=1 \
  FAISSR_REQUIRE_CUVS=1 \
  R CMD INSTALL .

Strict CUDA graph-clustering build:

  CUDA_HOME=/usr/local/cuda \
  FAISS_HOME=/path/to/faiss \
  CUGRAPH_HOME=/path/to/rapids-or-cugraph \
  FAISSR_REQUIRE_CUDA=1 \
  FAISSR_REQUIRE_CUGRAPH=1 \
  R CMD INSTALL .

The FAISSR_REQUIRE_* variables are aliases for requiring the corresponding
GPU feature at configure time. If a required GPU component is missing,
installation fails rather than producing a CPU-only build.

macOS
-----

macOS builds are expected to be CPU/FAISS builds. NVIDIA CUDA is not supported
on modern macOS/Apple Silicon systems. With Homebrew FAISS:

  brew install faiss libomp
  FAISS_HOME="$(brew --prefix faiss)" R CMD INSTALL .

Windows
-------

Automated Bioconductor/r-universe Windows builds are skipped because the
package is marked OS_type: unix. FAISS is mandatory and the Windows builders do
not provide a compatible FAISS development library.

Use Rtools and a FAISS build compiled with a compatible toolchain, or use WSL2
for Linux-style builds. Native RAPIDS cuVS/libcugraph C++ builds are generally
Linux-oriented; for NVIDIA GPU support on Windows, WSL2 is the recommended
route.

Bioconductor notes
------------------

Bioconductor and r-universe CPU builders need FAISS installed or FAISS_HOME set.
CUDA/cuVS/libcugraph should not be required on CPU-only builders. If NVIDIA GPU
support is required for a particular build environment, use the strict
FAISSR_REQUIRE_* variables above.
